* ============================================================
* INDEX X32 INX/CNX SMOKE v2
* ============================================================
* Purpose:
*   Test INX/CNX active-order behavior on x32 tables.
*
* Scope:
*   Non-destructive except disposable copy.
*   Uses X32.
*
* Key correction:
*   COPY TO requires the source table to remain open.
* ============================================================

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO INDEX X32 INX/CNX SMOKE v2
ECHO ============================================================

* Self-bootstrap without nested DOTSCRIPT dependency.
SET PATH DBF DBF/x32
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/x32
WORKSPACE CLOSE
ERASE students_x32_idxtest CONFIRM
WORKSPACE OPEN DBF

ECHO
ECHO --- SELECT STUDENTS X32 ---
SELECT STUDENTS
AREA
COUNT
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- PHYSICAL ORDER BASELINE ---
SETORDER 0
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
SKIP 1
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
BOTTOM
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- CNX ORDER LNAME ---
SETORDER students.cnx LNAME
AREA
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
SMARTLIST LNAME,FNAME,SID NEXT 10
SEEK WHITE
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
FIND MARTIN
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- CNX ORDER MAJOR ---
SETORDER students.cnx MAJOR
AREA
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
SMARTLIST MAJOR,LNAME,FNAME,SID NEXT 10

ECHO
ECHO --- MAKE DISPOSABLE X32 COPY ---
SELECT STUDENTS
COPY TO students_x32_idxtest WITH SIDECARS OVERWRITE
CLOSE
USE students_x32_idxtest
AREA
COUNT
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- CREATE/REINDEX INX ON LNAME ---
INDEX ON LNAME TAG students_x32_idxtest_lname.inx
REINDEX students_x32_idxtest_lname.inx
SETINDEX students_x32_idxtest_lname.inx
AREA
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
SKIP 10
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- ASC/DESC UNDER ACTIVE INX ---
ASCEND
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA
DESCEND
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- CLEAR ORDER ---
SETORDER 0
AREA
TOP
TUPLE SID,LNAME,FNAME,DOB,MAJOR,GPA

ECHO
ECHO --- CLOSE; CLEANUP MAY NEED MANUAL FILE ERASE IF ERASE TABLE DOES NOT FIND COPY ---
CLOSE
ERASE students_x32_idxtest CONFIRM
ECHO Suggested manual cleanup if needed:
ECHO ERASE students_x32_idxtest.dbf and students_x32_idxtest_lname.inx from X32 paths.

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO INDEX X32 INX/CNX SMOKE v2 DONE
ECHO ============================================================
